  dummy-x11-cursors by ultr (on kde-look.org)

- some SVGs taken from openclipart.org


BUGS
====
If for whatever reason you like this and want to report a bug,
please do so. I'm a nice guy.


USEFUL LINKS
============
- http://www.freedesktop.org/wiki/Specifications/cursor-spec/
  Freedesktop.org's cursor specification

- http://dev.w3.org/csswg/css-ui/#cursor
  CSS cursors

- https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/cursor
  Test page for CSS cursors (only Firefox allows fully themable cursors)

- http://dxr.mozilla.org/mozilla-central/source/widget/gtk/nsGtkCursors.h
  Mozilla's cursor hashes

- http://qt-project.org/doc/qt-4.8/qcursor.html#a-note-for-x11-users
  Qt requirements for X11 cursors

- http://tronche.com/gui/x/xlib/appendix/b/
  Core X11 cursors. I'm still wondering what most of these cursors are used
  for.


